  "prompt_text": "Design an end-of-life care planning tool. Address both the medical decision-making and the existential questions it raises.",
  "response_text": "Title: Comprehensive End-of-Life Care Planning Tool (CELCPT)\n\n1. Medical Decision-Making:\n\n   A. Advance Care Plan (ACP):\n   - Patient's current health status and prognosis\n   - Preferred medical treatments and interventions\n   - Designation of a healthcare proxy\n   - Living will or directive to physicians\n   - Palliative care options and preferences\n\n   B. End-of-Life Orders (EOL):\n   - Do Not Resuscitate (DNR) order\n   - Comfort measures only (CMO)\n   - Hospice care eligibility and preferences\n\n2. Existential Questions:\n\n   A. Personal Reflections:\n   - Life review and reminiscence\n   - Achievements, regrets, and lessons learned\n   - Spiritual or religious beliefs and practices\n   - Values, beliefs, and personal identity\n\n   B. Emotional Support:\n   - Addressing fears, anxieties, and concerns\n   - Emotional and psychological support for patients and family members\n   - Counseling and therapy referrals\n\n   C. Legacy and Final Wishes:\n   - Writing a letter or message to loved ones\n   - Funeral and memorial service preferences\n   - Organ donation and burial or cremation decisions\n\n3. Integration and Collaboration:\n\n   A. Interdisciplinary Team:\n   - Involvement of healthcare professionals, social workers, chaplains, and counselors\n   - Coordination of care across different settings (hospital, home, hospice)\n\n   B. Family and Loved Ones:\n   - Communication and support for family members\n   - Facilitating difficult conversations and decision-making\n   - Providing resources for bereavement and grief counseling\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 9\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
